[gd_scene load_steps=48 format=3]

; Dev-only greybox for the task-08 manual playtest (F6). Not wired into GameManager — mission
; flow is task 11. Move with WASD, look with the mouse, aim the + and press/HOLD [F] to pick up
; pocketable loot directly, bag loose cash/gold, drag the downed guard, or bank a haul at the
; Drop Point / Escape. [T] throws the carried bag, [G] puts down a dragged body, [K] is a
; debug-only "simulate a Catch" key. Fully operable now:
;   * JEWELRY CASE (silver): pocketable, grabbed directly — no bagging needed.
;   * CASH PILE / GOLD BAR: loose loot — the first [F] press bags it (occupies one hand); repeat
;     near either to add more loose loot to the same bag (still one hand).
;   * PAINTING (brown, SPECIAL tier, two-handed): delivering it to the Drop Point/Escape grants
;     a Stash trophy hook (FR-08-9).
;   * LOCK (gray door): consumable-pick counter-play — the Debug script hands it a real
;     PickPouch (task 06's stand-in, now backed by real inventory) and requests the task-07
;     lockpick overlay on interact.
;   * DROP POINT (green crate) / ESCAPE (blue door): bank everything currently carried —
;     immediately secured, survives a later Catch (press [K] to simulate one and watch the
;     readout: Secured stays, In-hand zeroes).
;   * GUARD (blue capsule, patrols the 3 waypoints; walk into its cone to get investigated —
;     see GuardGreybox for the full detection loop): once downed (task 10 owns the real takedown
;     input), its Body is draggable — dragging it grants vault_keycard (the Inspector keycard
;     pickup, ↩ from 05) and demonstrates BiometricLock's keyholder duck-type (purple device;
;     its required cfo_biometrics won't resolve against this guard's vault_keycard — it proves
;     the mechanism, not a solvable puzzle here, since no "cfo" EnemyDef exists yet).

